                        for my most oft used software, i use <a href="https://qutebrowser.org/">qutebrowser</a>, <a href="https://www.claws-mail.org/">claws mail</a>, 
                        <a href="https://heroicgameslauncher.com/">heroic games launcher</a>, and <a href="https://www.qownnotes.org/">qownnotes</a> (what i use to write blog posts).
                        i use <a href="https://sw.kovidgoyal.net/kitty/">kitty</a> with <a href="https://fishshell.com/">fish shell</a>. for programming and making this website i use <a href="https://vscodium.com/">vscodium</a> with vim keybinds; my general text editor is neovim.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        if i have anything to really recommend <em>specifically</em>, it'd have to be these. give them a try, i love them!
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>- <b><a href="https://qutebrowser.org/">qutebrowser</a></b> which is a minimalist browser that uses vim keybindings + is really fast</li>
                        <li>- <b><a href="https://github.com/jarun/nnn">nnn</a></b> which is a minimalist file manager. i used to use <a href="https://midnight-commander.org/">midnight commander</a> which is also great but nnn is so much quicker to use imo and it has all you need.</li>
                        <li>- <b><a href="https://johnfactotum.github.io/foliate/">foliate</a></b> which is imo the goat of linux e-readers</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>
